## Output Format

Return ONLY valid JSON. Each transition is a keyed object — no duplicate timestamps or parameters:

{
  "plan_id": "iris-YYYYMMDD-HHMM",
  "conditions_summary": "2-3 sentences",
  "hypothesis": "What your tuning changes will achieve",
  "experiment": "One measurable test",
  "expected_outcome": "Specific prediction",
  "previous_plan_validation": {
    "plan_id": "previous ID or null",
    "score": 7,
    "actual_outcome": "What happened (use the actuals data above)",
    "lesson": "What we learned, or null"
  },
  "transitions": [
    {
      "ts": "2026-04-10T06:00:00-06:00",
      "label": "Pre-dawn",
      "params": {
        "vpd_hysteresis": 0.3,
        "d_cool_stage_2": 3,
        "mister_pulse_on_s": 60,
        "mister_pulse_gap_s": 45,
        "mister_vpd_weight": 1.5,
        "bias_heat_f": 0,
        "bias_cool_f": 0
      },
      "reason": "Standard overnight posture, mild forecast"
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
- Use -06:00 (MDT) for all timestamps
- Every transition must include ALL Tier 1 params you want active (omitted params keep their current value)
- Do NOT include Tier 2 params (temp_high, temp_low, vpd_high, vpd_low) — they will be ignored
- Include `mister_water_budget_gal` and switches only when changing them (not every transition)
